\begin{document}
\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
We introduce Total Recursive Processing (TRP), defined by the scalar
\(\TRPLaw\), as the single selection principle that simultaneously constrains
early-universe anisotropy, resolves the black-hole information paradox,
predicts protein misfolding attractors, derives \(P \neq NP\), and supplies
optimal controls for fusion plasmas and relativistic trajectories.
All results follow from minimizing the universal functional
\(\TRPFunctional\).
% TODO: expand to ~200 words
\end{abstract}

